GUANGZHOU , February 20 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian today urged soldiers of the People 's Liberation Army -LRB- PLA -RRB- to pursue higher standards and build the army into one of the world 's first-class armies .
Chi , who is also a member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China -LRB- CPC -RRB- and chairman of the Central Military Committee , made the remarks during an inspection of the Shenzhen base of the PLA 's Hong Kong troops yesterday morning .
He spoke highly of the performance of the PLA 's Hong Kong troops during the past two years of their mission in Hong Kong , saying that the army has helped to successfully carry out the `` one country , two systems '' policy of the central government .
Chi also visited the Zhuhai base of the PLA 's Macao troops this morning .
`` History will remember the contributions made by the PLA soliders in Hong Kong and Macao , '' he said .
He stressed that the army must absolutely submit to the orders of the CPC .
`` This is an ultimate principle for the PLA , '' he said .
